<subSubSection id="C33F1AFCCC3EED04FF756E1AE40AFBE7" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9A4977CC3EED04FF756E1AE78CFC3F" blockId="4.[151,1436,656,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FF756E1AE42FFCCF" bold="true" box="[199,314,800,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is distinguished from 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FD486E1BE154FCCF" box="[762,1089,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
Dip. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2532F4CC3EED04FC806E1BE6F8FCCE" authority=", Dip." authorityName="Dip." box="[818,1005,801,825]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Diptilostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudipalpus">nudipalpus, Dip.</taxonomicName>
lofegoi
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FBC56E1BE1E0FCCE" box="[1143,1269,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Dip. mesae</emphasis>
by having: the opisthosomal setae 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FECA6E7CE491FCAB" box="[376,388,838,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">e</emphasis>
not extending beyond the bases of subsequent setae 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FC5E6E7FE6E1FCAB" box="[1004,1012,837,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">f</emphasis>
(setae 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FBFB6E7CE140FCAB" box="[1097,1109,838,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">e</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FBD56E7CE03CFCAB" box="[1127,1321,837,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
Dip. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2532F4CC3EED04FB106E7FE03CFCAB" authorityName="Ferla" authorityYear="2017" box="[1186,1321,837,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Diptilostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chimarricus">chimarricus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
30–40 vs others 40–60); setae 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FE376E53E486FC77" box="[389,403,873,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">d</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FE7C6E53E4FCFC77" box="[462,489,873,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">h2</emphasis>
much shorter, being 45–55 and 28–38, respectively (
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FBFC6E53E089FC77" box="[1102,1436,873,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
Dip. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2532F4CC3EED04FB3A6E53E053FC76" authority=", Dip." authorityName="Dip." box="[1160,1350,873,897]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Diptilostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudipalpus">nudipalpus, Dip.</taxonomicName>
lofegoi
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FF746EB4E450FC53" box="[198,325,910,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Dip. mesae</emphasis>
have setae 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FE756EB7E4C0FC53" box="[455,469,909,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">d</emphasis>
58–80 and 
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FDEB6EB7E760FC53" box="[601,629,909,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">h2</emphasis>
57–75); and leg I and II larger and with an 8–rayed empodium (smaller legs and 5–rayed empodium in other species).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9A4977CC3EED04FF756EEFE40AFBE7" blockId="4.[151,1436,656,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FF756EEFE493FC18" bold="true" box="[199,390,981,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Relation to host</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2532F4CC3EED04FE266EEFE7A1FC1B" authority="Ferla, 2017" authorityName="Ferla" authorityYear="2017" box="[404,692,981,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Diptilostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chimarricus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FE266EEFE7A1FC1B" box="[404,692,981,1005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Diptilostatus chimarricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A262281ECC3EED04FD0F6EEFE7E8FC18" box="[701,765,981,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FD0F6EEFE7E8FC18" bold="true" box="[701,765,981,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a leaf vagrant mite causing no obvious damage to yerba mate plants.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33F1AFCCC3EED04FF756927E7D4FBAF" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9A4977CC3EED04FF756927E7D4FBAF" blockId="4.[151,1436,656,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="B9519565CC3EED04FF756927E453FBC0" bold="true" box="[199,326,1053,1078]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Etymology</emphasis>
. The new species is named after a typical drink called “chimarrão” prepared with the leaves and drunk with hot water in Southern Cone countries.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
